Please enter a search query
---------------------------

[![Image 30](https://dblp.org/img/faq-mark.dark.12x12.png)](https://dblp.org/faq)

**see FAQ for more information**
*   [How to use the dblp search?](https://dblp.org/faq/1474589)
*   [Which technology does dblp use for searching the website?](https://dblp.org/faq/11960371)

*   _case-insensitive prefix search:_ default 

e.g., [sig](https://dblp.org/?q=sig) matches "SIGIR" as well as "signal"
*   _exact word search:_ append dollar sign ($) to word

e.g., [graph$](https://dblp.org/?q=graph$) matches "graph", but not "graphics"
*   _boolean and:_ separate words by space

e.g., [codd model](https://dblp.org/?q=codd%20model)
*   _boolean or:_ connect words by pipe symbol (|)

e.g., [graph|network](https://dblp.org/?q=graph%7Cnetwork)

Update May 7, 2017: Please note that we had to disable the _phrase search_ operator (.) and the _boolean not_ operator (-) due to technical problems. For the time being, phrase search queries will yield regular prefix search result, and search terms preceded by a minus will be interpreted as regular (positive) search terms.

About dblp
----------

The _dblp computer science bibliography_ provides open bibliographic information on major computer science journals and proceedings. Originally created at the [University of Trier](https://www.uni-trier.de/) in 1993, dblp is now operated and further developed by [Schloss Dagstuhl](https://www.dagstuhl.de/). For more information [check out our F.A.Q.](https://dblp.org/faq/)

dblp statistics
---------------

*   # of [publications](https://dblp.org/search/publ): 8,040,965
*   # of [authors](https://dblp.org/pers): 3,865,930
*   # of [conferences](https://dblp.org/db/conf): 6,933
*   # of [journals](https://dblp.org/db/journals): 1,881

*   % of publication types in dblp:

[![Image 56: publication types in dblp](https://dblp.org/statistics/img/distributionofpublicationtype.png)](https://dblp.org/statistics/distributionofpublicationtype)

[_more statistics_](https://dblp.org/statistics/)

XML data
--------

You may download the [raw dblp data in a single XML file](https://dblp.org/xml/). A simple DTD is available. The paper [DBLP - Some Lessons Learned](https://dblp.org/xml/docu/dblpxml.pdf) documents technical details of this XML file. In the appendix [DBLP XML Requests](https://dblp.org/xml/docu/dblpxmlreq.pdf) you may find the description of a primitive dblp query API. All metadata is released as open data under [CC0 1.0 license. ![Image 57: cc zero](https://dblp.org/img/cc0.80x15.black.png)](https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/)
